"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-01-team-gb-star-tears-interview-olympics-disqualification-21341043\", \"text\": \"Team GB'sEmma Reid was in tears after a disqualification ended her hopes of winning anOlympicmedal in the women's judo.  The 29-year-old, who won gold at theCommonwealth Gamestwo years ago, lost to South Korea's Hyunji Yoon\\u00a0in the opening round of the under-78kg event on Thursday morning.  Reid receiving two penalties inside the opening two minutes of the contest for non-combativity and a false attack before receiving her third during the golden score period - resulting in her disqualification.  Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  Reid's exit has now ended Team GB's chances of winning a judo medal in Paris.  'I think we had a really good preparation. We were at home, we went away for a camp. I just think it's tough, especially when a few of us, it's our first Games.  'We are not seeded so you can get anyone first fight. I have beaten her (Yoon) before so it's frustrating that I could have got to the next round but I think we all felt good going into it. It's just sometimes it does not happen on the day.'  Asked what she will do next, Reid replied: 'I think I will just reflect on the competition, I am just upset I could not make a better day of it.  'But rest and decompress from everything. It's been a tough three years, four years, well, my life really.  'I am just proud of myself for getting to this point\\u2026 sorry.'  Reid then covered her face as she began to cry before adding: 'Yeah, I think I am just going to rest up and go again.'  The BBC reporter attempted to console her by saying: 'You are an Olympian, no one can take that away from you.'  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Why is Matt Baker commentating on Olympic gymnastics?  ArrowMORE:Italian gymnast Giorgia Villa goes viral over parmesan cheese 